contents.headline: Madness '02 champs

photo.caption: Novi Madness ’02 fought all its way back from an opening-round loss to win seven straight game and claim the National Softball Association 12-and-under state championship which ended June 21 in East Lansing. Madness ’02 defeated the Devils ’02 twice to capture the title capped by a 10-2 victory in the finals after ralling twice from three runs down and scoring three times with two outs and nobody on base in the final inning of the first elimination game. Team members include (front row, from left): Angela Schmidt, Grace Nieto, Cassidy Brendtke, Stephanie Schmunk, Maggie Murphy; (back row, from left) Chelsea Collins, Gaby Cummings, Sierra Kersten, Abbey Barta, Olivia Vitale, McKenna King and Kylie Millhorn.

contents.headline: Madness '02 champs

photo.caption: Novi Madness ’02 fought all its way back from an opening-round loss to win seven straight game and claim the National Softball Association 12-and-under state championship which ended June 21 in East Lansing. Madness ’02 defeated the Devils ’02 twice to capture the title capped by a 10-2 victory in the finals after ralling twice from three runs down and scoring three times with two outs and nobody on base in the final inning of the first elimination game. Team members include (front row, from left): Angela Schmidt, Grace Nieto, Cassidy Brendtke, Stephanie Schmunk, Maggie Murphy; (back row, from left) Chelsea Collins, Gaby Cummings, Sierra Kersten, Abbey Barta, Olivia Vitale, McKenna King and Kylie Millhorn.
